        <font size='4'><b>CLINT BOWYER SPOTTED IN MILLSBERRY! </b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090212.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, February 12, 2009</b> &mdash;
    Millsberry citizens spotted a new face in the mix this week. And it just so happened to be that of famed racing champion, <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Clint Bowyer</a>!<br><br>No one was quite certain what <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Clint Bowyer</a> could be doing in Millsberry, but it soon became clear that he was up to something other than practicing his driving at the track. <br><br><a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Bowyer</a> was first seen in the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=4">Grocery Store</a>, doing some high-speed shopping.<br><br>&quot;I had never seen someone breeze through the store so quickly,&quot; said owner Harold Ettin. <br>
<br>
&quot;He did quick laps through the aisles with his cart, snagging food off the shelves at each turn. And he was finished in a matter of minutes. It&#039;s got to be some sort of record&mdash;grocery shopping that fast is unheard of,&quot; exclaimed Ettin. <br><br>As proof of his speed, <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Bowyer</a> was then spotted at several other locations in Millsberry&mdash;all within the very same hour. <br><br>&quot;I saw him enjoying the view at Lake Sylvane,&quot; said one citizen, &quot;and he looked speedy even standing still!&quot;<br><br>&quot;<a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Clint</a> was just walking down the street. I saw him. Then I blinked and he was gone,&quot; said Tania, owner of the Hair Salon. <br><br>&quot;It was the strangest thing. I&#039;ve never seen anyone take off so quickly,&quot; she added.  <br><br>Needless to say, rumors spread as people wondered what the racing star was doing in town. <br><br>As it happens, the <i>Gazette</i> was lucky enough to cross paths with <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Bowyer</a>. And, when asked what brought him to Millsberry, he responded, &quot;Mayor Wright asked me to come to Millsberry to help him out with a special project.&quot; <br><br>After jotting some notes in my pad, I was ready for my second question with the driving champ when I looked up to find that <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Clint</a> had vanished. It was easily the quickest interview I can remember.<br><br>Next, it was time to catch up with Mayor Wright, to see if he could shed some light on possible plans involving the unexpected, speedy visitor. <br><br>&quot;I can&#039; discuss any specifics at the moment,&quot; commented Wright, &quot;but I will say that what <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Clint Bowyer</a> and I are working on is sure to thrill the good citizens of Millsberry.&quot;<br><br><a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=clint_33">Bowyer</a> was last spotted with blueprints in his hand, heading into Town Hall with Mayor Wright.<br><br>Keep your eyes peeled! You never know what may be coming our way. <br>
    </div>

